HEADWORD: Palmaceae
<hw>Palmaceae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A natural family of chiefly
tropical trees and shrubs and vines usually having a tall columnar trunk
bearing a crown of very large leaves; coextensive with the order
<ord>Palmales</ord>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Palmae, family <fam>Palmae</fam>, family
<fam>Palmaceae</fam>, Arecaceae, family <fam>Arecaceae</fam>, palm
family.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palmaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
